<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-1057 </DOCNO><TEXT>With the results of about 600 hip joint prostheses examined by scintigraphy,it is evident that nuclear medicine is more than a supplementary examination,especially in the case of a non-cemented isoelastic prosthesis. The combinationof 3-phase scintigraphy with leucocyte scintigraphy could solve the problemsof infected and aseptic displaced prostheses in 90% of the cases. Theconventional X-ray diagnostic being the only method to demonstrate bonemorphology is still the primary examination.</TEXT></DOC>